<p>On 2 December 2011 the European Evaluation Society (EES) Seminar ‘The vision and logic of evaluation’ was held in the Centre for Fine Arts in Brussels. The EES has provided several videos from this one-day event. The recordings of the presentations (listed here) as well as discussions and the closing panel discussion are available at the link listed below:</p>
<list id="list1-1356389012444961" list-type="bullet">
<list-item><p>Nicoletta Stame – ‘Evaluation and learning in the current crisis’</p></list-item>
<list-item><p>Evert O Vedung – ‘Four waves of evaluation diffusion: Or is there a fifth wave around?’</p></list-item>
<list-item><p>Frans L Leeuw – ‘Theories in and for evaluation: Why, how and what about the future?’</p></list-item>
</list>
<p>To view these, see: <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://www.europeanevaluation.org/conferences/ees-conferences-and-events/past-ees-conferences/1319097893-ees-seminar-the-vision-and-logic-of-evaluation/ees-seminar-video-recording.htm">http://www.europeanevaluation.org/conferences/ees-conferences-and-events/past-ees-conferences/1319097893-ees-seminar-the-vision-and-logic-of-evaluation/ees-seminar-video-recording.htm</ext-link></p>
